TextEng: Could I ask you some questions?
Text: 몇 가지 질문 좀 해도 될까요?

TextEng: Uh... Me ask questions?
Goodbye.
Yes, the wolves. What can you tell me about them?
Text: 그래요, 늑대들 말입니다. 그것들에 대해 뭘 알려주실 수 있나요?

TextEng: Actually I'm hunting down a cult...
How many of you live here?
Anything interesting going on in these parts?
Text: 이 근처에서 흥미로운 일이 일어나고 있나요?

TextEng: Yuh, da wolves. What you know of them?
Uh, me be huntin' down a cult...
This be small house. How many live here?
Text: 이 작은 집. 몇 명 살아?

TextEng: You know odd things about here?
Maybe I can help. Know anything else about it?
Text: 제가 도와드릴 수 있을지도 모르겠네요. 그것에 대해 더 아는 게 있나요?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> Cattle cost money. How bad are the finances?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 소는 돈이 드는데. 재정 상황이 얼마나 나쁩니까?

TextEng: Maybe me help, yuh? You talk more 'bout it.
Text: 나 도와줄 수 있어, 응? 그거 더 얘기해.

TextEng: Tell me about the wolves, then.
I'd be interested in work, if you know of anything.
Are there any other places you think I should stop by, here?
Text: 여기서 제가 들러봐야 할 다른 곳이 있을까요?

TextEng: Yuh, tell me story 'bout Peter and da Wolf!
Me want work.
There be other places to go here?
How is Constance?
How Constance be?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Come now, telling me won't do any harm.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이봐요, 말해줘도 아무런 해가 없을 텐데요.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Tell me. Will hurt nobody.
I'm curious about some recent events...
Text: 최근 사건들에 대해 궁금한 게 있는데요...

TextEng: There be stuff happening lately, yuh?
I want to ask you something else.
Me have other question.
Can I ask you some directions?
Uh, me lost. You give directions, yuh?
Text: 어, 나 길 잃었어. 길 알려줘, 응?

TextEng: Where does the west road lead?
Where does the east road lead?
Is there a place to buy equipment nearby?
Text: 근처에 장비 살 수 있는 곳이 있나요?

TextEng: Where that west road go?
Where that east road go?
Me need place to buy stuff.
Actually, I'd rather ask you about something else.
Me have other question.

Me need more directions.
